# Frontend Routing & Layout Scaffold (Issue #29 / S1-4a)

This PR will set up the foundational frontend routing architecture using `react-router-dom`. It establishes the main routing configuration, the global application layout (including a persistent navigation bar), and placeholder components for the upcoming features in Sprints 1 & 2.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [NEW] `client/src/router.jsx`
- Define the routing configuration using `createBrowserRouter` from `react-router-dom`.
- Set up a root route with a `Layout` component that acts as an ErrorBoundary for uncaught errors, and an `errorElement` for 404s.
- Add child routes for `/`, `/create`, `/logs/:id`, and `/profile/:username`.

#### [MODIFY] [client/src/main.jsx](file:///Users/mineral/Desktop/VibeCoding/P2/cs7180_project2_collective-unconscious/client/src/main.jsx)
- Replace `<App />` with `<RouterProvider router={router} />`.

### Components
#### [NEW] `client/src/components/Layout.jsx`
- Create a persistent wrapper component for the app.
- Include a `<nav>` with `Link` and `NavLink` elements pointing to the placeholder routes based on the design specified in the [App.jsx](file:///Users/mineral/Desktop/VibeCoding/P2/cs7180_project2_collective-unconscious/client/src/App.jsx) prototype.
- Include an `<Outlet />` wrapper for child route content.

### Pages (Placeholders)
#### [NEW] `client/src/pages/HomePage.jsx`
- Placeholder component for the Discovery Feed.

#### [NEW] `client/src/pages/CreateLogPage.jsx`
- Placeholder component for the Log Creation page.

#### [NEW] `client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx`
- Placeholder component for viewing a specific log / write zone. Extracts the `:id` parameter using `useParams()`.

#### [NEW] `client/src/pages/UserProfilePage.jsx`
- Placeholder component for the User Profile. Extracts the `:username` parameter.

#### [NEW] `client/src/pages/NotFoundPage.jsx`
- A generic 404 page ("Not Found") that displays when a user hits an undefined route.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
#### [NEW] `client/src/__tests__/routing.test.jsx`
- First, write a test suite using `vitest` and `@testing-library/react` that checks if the `RouterProvider` correctly renders the `Layout` and navigation links.
- Test that clicking navigation links simulates route changes without full page reloads.
- Test that an invalid path renders the `NotFoundPage` component.
- The tests will be written and run **first** following the project's Test-Driven Development (TDD) mandate.

**Command to run tests:**
```bash
cd client
npm run test
```

### Manual Verification
- Run `npm run dev` in the `client` directory.
- Open the application in the browser and verify the global navbar is visible.
- Click the "Feed" and "Write" links in the navbar to see the URL update to `/` and `/create` (or whatever path is designated), while the page content updates instantly.
- Manually navigate to a fake URL (e.g., `http://localhost:5173/fake-url`) and verify the 404 page is displayed.
